neuralNetwork

Class Network

  • Object
    • Network

  • public class Network
extends Object
    This class creates a neural network with 3 layers: an input layer, hidden layer and output layer.
    Author:
    franciscogonzalez08 and drophy at GitHub

    • Constructor Detail

      • Network

        public Network(int inputSize,
               int outputSize)
        Constructs a network with the specified number of neurons for the input and output layers. The number of neurons the hidden layer has is obtained as ceil((inputSize + outputSize)/2.0), which is the recommended size for this layer. Its learning rate will be set to 0.1 which is its highest possible value. This allows the network to learn faster (require less training to get good results), but may perform poorly compared to a network with a lower learning rate.
        Parameters:
        inputSize - size of the input layer
        outputSize - size of the output layer

      • Network

        public Network(int inputSize,
               int outputSize,
               double learning_rate)
        Constructs a network with the specified learning rate and number of neurons for the input and output layers. The number of neurons the hidden layer has is obtained as ceil((inputSize + outputSize)/2.0), which is the recommended size for this layer.
        Parameters:
        inputSize - size of the input layer
        outputSize - size of the output layer
        learning_rate - number in range [0.001, 0.1] that specifies how strongly this network is affected by a training case

      • Network

        middleNeurons - size of the hidden layer
        outputSize - size of the output layer
        learning_rate - number in range [0.001, 0.1] that specifies how strongly this network is affected by a training case

    • Method Detail

      • configureMapping

        public void configureMapping(Map<String,Integer> m)
        By default, the network is configured so that the outputs correspond to a 0 based base 10 number. In any other scenario, the user must provide a map with the class (as a String) as its key and 0 based indexes as its values.
        Parameters:
        m - map of classes (key) to indexes (value)

      • trainCSV

        public void trainCSV(String path,
                     int from,
                     int to)
        Trains this network using the file specified in "path". Only the rows in the range specified by "from" and "to" will be used. The file must be a CSV file with a row per training case. The first column of each row must contain the class the image belongs to. The following columns must contain a value in range [0, 255] corresponding to the greyscale value of a pixel. Pixels are expected to be ordered as consecutive rows of the original image.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the CSV file
        from - first row that will be used
        to - last row that will be used

      • trainCSV

        public void trainCSV(String path,
                     int quantity)
        Trains this network using the file specified in "path" and the first "quantity" rows. The file must be a CSV file with a row per training case. The first column of each row must contain the class the image belongs to. The following columns must contain a value in range [0, 255] corresponding to the greyscale value of a pixel. Pixels are expected to be ordered as consecutive rows of the original image.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the CSV file
        quantity - number of rows that will be used from the CSV file

      • trainCSV

        public void trainCSV(String path)
        Trains this network using the file specified in "path". The file must be a CSV file with a row per training case. The first column of each row must contain the class the image belongs to. The following columns must contain a value in range [0, 255] corresponding to the greyscale value of a pixel. Pixels are expected to be ordered as consecutive rows of the original image.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the CSV file

      • testCSV

        public double[] testCSV(String path,
                        int from,
                        int to)
        Tests the accuracy of the network using the file specified in "path". Only the rows in the range specified by "from" and "to" will be used. The method will print in the console the number of cases this network solved correctly. The file must be a CSV file with a row per training case. The first column of each row must contain the class the image belongs to. The following columns must contain a value in range [0, 255] corresponding to the greyscale value of a pixel. Pixels are expected to be ordered as consecutive rows of the original image.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the CSV file
        from - first row that will be used
        to - last row that will be used
        Returns:
        An array with the inverse of the average error of each output. Note that while higher values do correlate to a better performance, high values are usually obtained regardless of the network's accuracy.

      • testCSV

        public double[] testCSV(String path,
                        int quantity)
        Tests the accuracy of the network using the file specified in "path" and the first "quantity" rows. The method will print in the console the number of cases this network solved correctly. The file must be a CSV file with a row per training case. The first column of each row must contain the class the image belongs to. The following columns must contain a value in range [0, 255] corresponding to the greyscale value of a pixel. Pixels are expected to be ordered as consecutive rows of the original image.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the CSV file
        quantity - number of rows that will be used from the CSV file
        Returns:
        An array with the inverse of the average error of each output. Note that while higher values do correlate to a better performance, high values are usually obtained regardless of the network's accuracy.

      • testCSV

        public double[] testCSV(String path)

The file must be a CSV file with a row per training case. The first column of each row must contain the class the image belongs to. The following columns must contain a value in range [0, 255] corresponding to the greyscale value of a pixel. Pixels are expected to be ordered as consecutive rows of the original image.

      • evaluateIMG

        public void evaluateIMG(String path)
        Receives an image and prints to the console the network's guess. A line is printed per possible class. Each line contains the class's index followed by a number in range [0, 1]. The higher the number, the more certain the network is that the image given belongs to that class. The image must have exactly as many pixels as the input layer.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the image

      • save

        public void save(String path_name)
        Creates a .txt file containing the current configuration of the network. The file can be used by the load static method to create an identical network. This is specially useful so that the network's training is not lost after the application's execution ends.
        Parameters:
        path_name - path and name for the new file

      • load

        public static Network load(String path)
        Creates and returns a neural network with the configuration given by the specified .txt file. Such a file can be created using the save method on an already existing neural network.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the .txt file
        Returns:
        a new neural network object with the configuration given by the specified .txt file.
